### What problem does this feature solve?
```javascript

exports._initData = function () {
  var propsData = this._data
  var optionsDataFn = this.$options.data
  var optionsData = optionsDataFn && optionsDataFn()
  if (optionsData) {
    this._data = optionsData
    for (var prop in propsData) {
      if (process.env.NODE_ENV !== 'production' &&
          optionsData.hasOwnProperty(prop)) {
        _.warn(
          'Data field "'   prop   '" is already defined '  
          'as a prop. Use prop default value instead.'
        )
      }
//...

```

When _initData initializes, it will make a decision on propsData，According to my understanding, propsData should be an empty object at this time.

### What does the proposed API look like?
According to my understanding, the content of _data mainly comes from two aspects：On the one hand, component custom data. On the other hand, the prop directive calls initProp when executing `bind`. But for the second case，The prop instruction is executed at the time of _initScope，This time point is a bit later than __initData. So I don't quite understand why want to make a decision on `propsData` when _initData is initialized to avoid overwriting.

